comments: Haliburton (IND) extends his left hand into Vucevic's (CHI) side and the contact after the gather impacts Vucevic's driving shot attempt.

Nesmith's (IND) forearm comes forward slightly and marginal contact occurs with White's (CHI) head/face as he dribbles.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
DeRozan (CHI) and Haliburton (IND) briefly engage and disengage off-ball.
Haliburton (IND) steps forward toward DeRozan (CHI) and marginal contact occurs prior to DeRozan releasing his desired pass.
Vucevic (CHI) firms up in Nesmith's (IND) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.
Caruso (CHI) briefly grasps Brown's (IND) arm and marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
DeRozan (CHI) brushes Haliburton's (IND) arm and marginal contact occurs as Haliburton completes his desired pass.
Nesmith (IND) jumps forward into LaVine's (CHI) body and initiates contact that dislodges him from his rebounding position.
Caruso (CHI) contests to Haliburton's (IND) side and incidental "high-five" contact occurs after the release.
Haliburton (IND) overtly brings his leg towards Caruso (CHI), and the contact after the release is marginal.
LaVine (CHI) and Nembhard (IND) come together during the pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs.
Hield (IND) and LaVine (CHI) come together at the same spot on the floor and the contact on the play is marginal.  Hield also does not intentionally kick the ball away from LaVine.
LaVine (CHI) signals for, and is awarded, a timeout prior to the tie-up with Nembhard (IND).

Following a review of the confrontation between LaVine (CHI) and Nehmhard (IND), LaVine is assessed and unsportsmanlike technical foul for verbally taunting Nemhard. All technical fouls are subsequently reviewed by the League Office.
Caruso (CHI) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Caruso (CHI) is moving alongside Nembhard's (IND) path and marginal contact occurs with Nembhard's side during the drive.
Haliburton (IND) brings his hand toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with White's (CHI) arm prior to the release of the pass.
LaVine (CHI) deflects the pass off of his left hand prior to legally gathering the ball.  Upon gaining full control, LaVine legally begins his dribble.

Replay review of the foul called on Nembhard (IND) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Nembhard extends his leg forward into Caruso's (CHI) path and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Vucevic (CHI) places his hands momentarily on Turner's (IND) side and marginal contact occurs as they move in the same direction off-ball.
Vucevic (CHI) legally contests Turner's (IND) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Hield (IND) legally saves the ball back in play before his foot comes down out of bounds.
Hield (IND) does not step out of bounds while in possession of the ball.

Replay review of the foul called on DeRozan (CHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. DeRozan avoids making contact with Hield (IND) as he contests the jump shot attempt. At the time of the whistle, Chicago is deemed to have imminent possession and play resumes with possession awarded to Chicago.
Caruso (CHI) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Brown (IND) applies his hand to DeRozan's (CHI) side and marginal contact occurs as they move in the same direction off ball.
LaVine (CHI) and Nembhard (IND) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Nembhard (IND) briefly grasps LaVine's (CHI) left arm, and the marginal contact occurs as Nembhard's right hand simultaneously deflects the inbound pass away from LaVine.
Nembhard (IND) extends his arm forward and makes contact with LaVine (CHI) that affects his SQBR.
